added.title: Spring Beak
added.description: Plucky goes home with Babs and Buster for Spring Break and quickly becomes the new star of Burrowville, while Hamton and Sweetie embark on the adventure after accidently missing their train stop.

removed.title: Crushing Defeat
removed.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

removed.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
removed.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

removed.title: Camp Unikitty
removed.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

removed.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
removed.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

removed.title: Haunted Campfire
removed.description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

removed.title: Cheerleading
removed.description: Brock drags Master Frown along to join him in following his dream, to become the Flyer on a cheerleading team. They team up with Unikitty & the gang and go head to head against Really Old Edith and her rival cheer team of meanies. But when the gang finds Brock is too heavy to be the Flyer they're forced to try a bunch of ridiculous ways to get him off the ground.

removed.title: Last One There
removed.description: When Unikitty accidentally invokes an ancient curse, the gang must beat Master Frown and Brock back to the castle before one of them literally turns into a rotten egg.

removed.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays
removed.description:
Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day./
Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

removed.title: The Big Trip
removed.description: It's time for the gang's yearly vacation, but Hawk refuses to go, claiming the gang's vacations are never fun for him because the others are terrible at vacationing. Hawk only agrees to go if the gang pass his super-intense vacation training course.

removed.title: Hawkodile Sensei
removed.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

removed.title: Action Forest
removed.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

removed.title: The Ranch
removed.description: The Titans must help the crew of Teen Titans Go! move to their new offices.

removed.title: Scary Tales 2
removed.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

removed.title: Cosmic Bupkiss
removed.description: A storm blocks Oscar and Hedgehog's one chance to see a comet.

removed.title: Sunken Treasure
removed.description: A relaxing beach day becomes an underwater adventure when Unikitty and her friends find a message in a bottle.

removed.title: Lab Cat
removed.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

removed.title: Too Cool
removed.description: Puppycorn needs a lesson in how to be cool. The gang is more than happy to teach him, until his coolness unexpectedly freezes the whole kingdom.

removed.title: The Unikingdom Awards
removed.description: Unikitty throws an elaborate award show for everyone in the Unikingdom, including Master Frown and Brock, but tensions rise when Frown fails to win an award.

removed.title: Wiener Club
removed.description: Puppycorn is determined to become the Hot Dog King and joins an underground hot dog eating contest called Weiner Club. Rick warns "you are what you eat," but Puppycorn doesn't listen and eats so many hot dogs he becomes the new champion of Weiner Club. Unfortunately he also literally turns into a hot dog, that the other club members reveal they are going to eat! Unikitty and the gang now must attack with vegetables and defeat the hot dog-eating baddies in order to save the giant hot-dog-shaped Puppycorn and turn him back to normal.

removed.title: Career Day
removed.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

removed.title: Tragic Magic
removed.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

removed.title: Late Night Talky Time
removed.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

removed.title: Bedtime Stories
removed.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

removed.title: R & Arr
removed.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

removed.title: The Zone
removed.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

removed.title: The Prince and the Squeak of Obedience
removed.description: Feral and her gang of cat-thieves have stolen Prince Ivandoe's map to Eagle Mountain. Cupcake, the pink-poodle survivalist offers to train Prince Ivandoe to become a Jungle Warrior. So that together they can infiltrate Feral's camp and get back whats theirs. For Feral also stole a precious item from Cupcake... one that exerts a strange hold over him - "The Squeak of Obedience!"
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: Cast Aside the Truth
removed.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

removed.title: Memory Amok
removed.description: When Puppycorn witnesses Unikitty do the most embarrassing thing ever, he vows he will never forget it. Desperate, Unikitty uses Dr. Fox's memory machine to erase Puppycorn's memory of the embarrassing event. In the process, Unikitty accidentally releases all of Puppycorn's memories. Now she and the gang must scramble to capture all the scampering memories, or Puppycorn will forget his life.

removed.title: Dancer Danger
removed.description: Unikingdom's throwing a kingdom-wide dance, a fun event where everyone dresses up and busts a move. Everyone's excited... except for Richard, who's terrified to let loose and feel his inner groove. Unikitty knows Rick needs to express himself but can she and the others convince him to break out of his shell with some minor robotic body enhancements?

removed.title: No Day Like Snow Day
removed.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

removed.title: Last Laugh
removed.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

removed.title: P.L.O.T. Device 2: Beyond the Bored Dome
removed.description: Dr. Fox reprograms the P.L.O.T. Device to only generate boring events, but the gang can't help but add drama and excitement to every scenario.

removed.title: Tell-A-Photo/Born to Sing (song)/Move It!
removed.description: Tell-A-Photo: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together./Move It!: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

removed.title: Tooned In Space
removed.description: The toons take Marvin the Martian's class, and head to space. Buster tries to cheer up a homesick Babs, Plucky searches for a space outfit, and Sweetie is too obsessed with a video game to notice any of it - even when the aliens attack!

removed.title: The Littlest Tweety/Over the Burrow (song)/In Bugs We Trust
removed.description: The Littlest Tweety: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size./In Bugs We Trust: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

removed.title: Grown Up Stuff
removed.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

removed.title: Broken Ducky/ Watermelon Rescue/ New Birdy
removed.description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures with a ducky toy, working as a team, and learning to share the spotlight.

removed.title: One Ripe Tomato
removed.description: When Vivie disagrees with her friends about who gets to use a ripe garden tomato, Barney creates space for everyone to share their ideas. Vivie realizes it's important to share and they use the tomato to make a pizza everyone can enjoy.

removed.title: Best Best Friends
removed.description: Master Frown and Brock attend a friendship-themed competition intending to ruin it for everyone else, but soon discover their own friendship in need of repair.

removed.title: Hide N' Seek
removed.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

removed.title: Ragtag
removed.description: When the kingdom runs out of inspiration, Unikitty takes it on herself to re-inspire the citizens with a riveting game of kickball where she and the gang form a ragtag team of underdogs, who are supposed to win a miraculous unexpected victory against Master Frown, Brock & The Doom Lords. But when the Doom Lords end up stinking at kickball, and the people are uninspired by the good guys' easy victory, Unikitty switches things up and joins the real ragtag team, The Doom Lords, to help lead them to a victory that finally inspires the kingdom.

removed.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
removed.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

removed.title: Chair
removed.description: Unikitty finds an old, beatup recliner on the curb, but sees its inner beauty and brings it home to introduce to the gang! In a series of absurd and fun vignettes, we discover how a dirty, inanimate chair comes into each of their lives and changes them for the better. We soon learn that dear, sweet Chair was too good for this world.

removed.title: Asteroid Blues
removed.description: An asteroid is headed right for the kingdom, so Dr Fox leads the gang on a mission to save the kingdom by flying a rocket to the asteroid's surface and blowing it to bits with a huge bomb. But when they get there the gang finds the lonely asteroid is actually a super nice guy and don't want to blow him up.

removed.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
removed.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

removed.title: Double Daddies Day/The Pickle Fixer
removed.description: Apple double-duty organizes Father's Day for her two Dads. Will she crush it or face a Double Daddies Day Disaster? On Dad's first day as a stay-at-home parent, Stellar plays teacher to show him parenting is a breeze!

removed.title: Too Many Unikittys
removed.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

removed.title: Fruit Caboose/ Bin Bug/ Bug Hugs
removed.description: The bugs learn about sharing, Lu hogs the funnest role in a game, and Barnaby learns about sharing hugs.

removed.title: Special Delivery
removed.description: After being rudely interrupted by Bim Bom during her daily morning song, an angry Unikitty takes the advice of her friends and writes down her feelings into a letter with the intention of keeping the letter to herself, but then accidentally sends it off, complete with postage! The gang then goes on a wild chase through the Unikingdom mail delivery service to keep that rude letter from getting into the hands of Bim Bom, and ultimately hurting her feelings. Turns out, Unikitty's "rude" is everyone else's "nice" and the letter was full of compliments.

removed.title: Brawl Bot
removed.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

removed.title: Delivery Effect
removed.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

removed.title: Wishing Well
removed.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

removed.title: The Escape Room of Doom
removed.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

removed.title: Baby Caterpillar
removed.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

removed.title: Rainbow Race
removed.description: Sadness levels have hit an all-time low in Frowntown. In an attempt to cheer up the citizens of the town, Unikitty and the gang load a rainbow into a tanker truck with the intention of releasing it over Frowntown. Now they must avoid the marauding Master Frown in his monster truck, to succeed.

removed.title: Unfairgrounds
removed.description: Unikitty and her friends have an exciting day at their favorite amusement park/carnival boardwalk but Frown and Brock are there to ruin their good times and drive everyone out! The park owner warns Unikitty that if attendance keeps dropping the pier ​will close forever! Can the friends take charge, save the park, and find out Master Frown's secret ​motives? What a roller coaster of emotions!

removed.title: No Sleep Sleepover
removed.description: It's a sleepover at the castle and Unikitty and Puppycorn want to stay up all night, believing something magical must happen if you stay up long enough.​ At first the friends are game to stay up all night, but as they fall asleep one by one, Unikitty worries they won't make it! How far will she and her bro go to stay awake, and will they discover the secret reason people are supposed to go to bed when the Sandman shows up?

removed.title: Paddle Field Earth
removed.description: Today's challenge involves canoeing, hiking and mountain climbing. It's just like normal summer camp!! Except that you canoe over a waterfall, hike through a geyser field and climb a mountain that's actually the world's biggest beehive. It's nothing like summer camp.

removed.title: Top of the Naughty List
removed.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

removed.title: The Prince and the Playdate
removed.description: Prince Ivandoe is a prisoner in the castle dungeon of Jezabel's mother, Grizabella - the unpredictable and slightly terrifying "Queen of Thieves". Whilst waiting for a royal random, Grizabella encourages her daughter to enjoy her "playdate" with the little prince. Prince Ivandoe is all too eager to do the same. However, when Grizabella demands that Prince Ivandoe perform as her Royal Jester - Ivandoe and Bert realise they need to escape. At once!!
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: Tasty Heist
removed.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

removed.title: Slay Cheese
removed.description: It's picture day at Acme Loo! Babs accidentally shrinks herself, Buster fails to get the perfect photo day haircut, Plucky gives lessons on being direct, and Hamton struggles to find his photo persona.

removed.title: Kevin 11
removed.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

removed.title: Perfect Moment
removed.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

removed.title: Pet Pet
removed.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

removed.title: Tourist Trap
removed.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

removed.title: Kitchen Chaos
removed.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

removed.title: Growing Pains
removed.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

removed.title: Brock Most Wanted
removed.description: When Master Frown starts ruining parties to earn a promotion from his bosses, the Doom Lords, Brock accidentally gets blamed for the calamity. He helps Frown ruin more parties to clear his name and prove he's not the real party pooper, but before long Brock is the most notorious criminal in the kingdom, and the Doom Lords hire him as Master Party Pooper. Desperate to get his promotion and save his friend, Master Frown recruits Unikitty to ruin one last party, Brock's Doom Lord initiation ceremony.

removed.title: The New Nemesis
removed.description: When Hawkodile discovers his old enemy Eagleator has a new nemesis in his life, the gang do all they can to get Hawk back on his foe's radar.

removed.title: Roadtrip Ruckus
removed.description: Richard has decided to take Unikitty and the gang for a pleasant and relaxing 10 hour road trip. At first everyone is against the trip, but they soon start to have fun. Unfortunately, their idea of fun is not Richard's.  He soon begins to give in to his inner road-rage. To make matters worse they are being chased by a killer semi-truck, and their car has been invaded by weird bug hitchhiker.  Will Richard loose it, or will the trip be a great success?

removed.title: Cool for Cats/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Time Out!
removed.description: Cool for Cats: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool./Time Out!: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

removed.title: Who Took Toast
removed.description: When Toast disappears from Unikitty's party she leads a search to find him and expose the toast-napper.

removed.title: Big Pup, Little Problem
removed.description: After a mishap in the lab, everyone in the castle- except for Puppycorn- is shrunk to tiny size! Puppycorn thinks it's cool. His friends are like living action figures! So he begins playing with them in imaginary adventures. Unikitty and the others think being miniature and playing with Puppycorn is surprisingly fun, but PC has a habit of accidentally breaking his toys, and it's soon clear the gang will have to make a daring, tiny escape back to the lab before Puppycorn loves them to pieces!

removed.title: Welcome to the Unikingdom
removed.description: After Unikitty finds out that tourism is down in the Unikingdom, she recruits the gang to make a tourism video to inspire people to visit the kingdom. But after calamities come one after another, Unikitty begins to think the video is going to turn out to be a disaster. However the friends save the day with some creativity and manage to get a single tourist to visit. Mission accomplished!

removed.title: The Prince and the Princenappers
removed.description: Whilst travelling through the notoriously dangerous Forest of Outlaws, Prince Ivandoe is repeatedly Princenapped! First by a gang of wolves in disguise, then by Boaris and his Merry Boars, and finally by Feral and her gang of cat-thieves - all of them hoping to secure a royal ransom. Luckily for Prince Ivandoe and Bert, they are rescued by the fair Jezabel - though, as it turns out, not with the noblest of intentions.
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: The Alliance
removed.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

removed.title: Super Amazing Raft Adventure
removed.description: Unikitty and Hawkodile are "lost at sea", stranded on a raft together. Hawkodile sees this as an opportunity to show Unikitty that he's prepared for anything with his expertly-honed survival skills, but to his shock, all of his plans keep falling apart, while Unikitty's silly "it'll all work out, let's have fun" approach is somehow working great! Will Hawkodile manage to let go of his overpreparedness to save them both, or will Unikitty whimsical fun be their doom?

removed.title: Kitty & Hawk
removed.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

removed.title: Unikitty News!
removed.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

removed.title: Landlord Lord
removed.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

removed.title: Lucky Girl
removed.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

removed.title: Prank War
removed.description: When Master Frown starts a prank war with UniKingdom, the friends are ready to strike back. But Unikitty doesn't really understand pranks, thinking they're too mean. Can the friends help Unikitty comprehend a proper goof and win the prank war with Frown? Or will they be forced to suffer his tricks without retaliation and admit defeat?

removed.title: This Spells Disaster
removed.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

removed.title: Safety First
removed.description: Concerned about Puppycorn's propensity to hurt himself constantly, the gang places him into Richard's old Safety Suit. The suit does indeed keep him safe, but when Puppycorn purposefully puts himself in danger the suit goes into lock down, and won't allow him to move. Now the gang must figure out a way to get him out of the Safety Suit.

removed.title: Dinner Apart-y
removed.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

removed.title: License to Punch
removed.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

removed.title: BatKitty
removed.description: The gang are at the local laundromat cleaning their clothes, when Unikitty finds Batman's uniform mixed in with her clothes.  Intoxicated by the coolness of it, Unikitty takes on the persona of Batman and begins to fight crime.  When she accidentally causes Master Frown to step up his crime game, she will need the help of her friends, dressed as Robin, to stop him.

removed.title: Buggin' Out
removed.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

removed.title: Fire & Nice
removed.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

removed.title: Tortoise Rigamortis
removed.description: With just 5 campers remaining things are getting tense. So today is just about having fun taking selfies with wild animals. Everyone had their rabies shot?

removed.title: Beach Daze
